{"data":{"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"725e8d29-2fe6-59de-991f-3734d2f7cf6d","html":"<h2>Yay!!</h2>\n<p>Images are linked externally via relative path, seems to be affected by <code>gatsby-config.js</code> path which should match something eelse.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1cf93e02b30f3cae8cd703a69b14f478/d3c45/test.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.1081081081081%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Me when alt\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/1cf93e02b30f3cae8cd703a69b14f478/1c72d/test.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1cf93e02b30f3cae8cd703a69b14f478/a80bd/test.jpg 148w,\n/static/1cf93e02b30f3cae8cd703a69b14f478/1c91a/test.jpg 295w,\n/static/1cf93e02b30f3cae8cd703a69b14f478/1c72d/test.jpg 590w,\n/static/1cf93e02b30f3cae8cd703a69b14f478/a8a14/test.jpg 885w,\n/static/1cf93e02b30f3cae8cd703a69b14f478/fbd2c/test.jpg 1180w,\n/static/1cf93e02b30f3cae8cd703a69b14f478/d3c45/test.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://history-computer.com/ModernComputer/Basis/images/Engelbart.jpg\" alt=\"Engelbart\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1>Publish once completed!</h1>\nLinks work as so but of course page must exists: <a href=\"/Projects\" title=\"Projects\">Projects</a>","parent":{"name":"Big Chungus"}}},{"node":{"id":"8afc8aa7-794b-5d06-bde7-b2baa8b8ed16","html":"<h1>Black Pepper Beef Soup</h1>\n<p>If you <em>really</em> like black pepper, this soup may be for you.</p>\n<h2>Ingredients</h2>\n<h2>Method</h2>\n<h2>Notes</h2>\n<p>Adapted Andy Cooks Yukgaejang but skipped the gochugaru/garlic/sesame oil and fernbrake, and added 1/4-1/2 cup black peppercorns.</p>\n<p>I tasted it and I think it needs an additional ingredient and accent flavor to round it out. Also add herbs next time.  Filter the peppercorns after the broth is done.</p>\n<p>Suggested pairings:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Garlic</li>\n<li>Basil</li>\n<li>Ginger</li>\n<li>Parsley</li>\n<li>Thyme</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Peas, scallions, spinach as vegetables</p>\n<p>Radishes maybe too as garnish</p>\n<a href=\"/Big Chungus\" title=\"Big Chungus\">Big Chungus</a>","parent":{"name":"Black Pepper Beef Soup"}}}]}}}